narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would encourage anyone to take this class. If only to balance out the insanity of your other coursework. I really enjoyed being stretched in new ways through engaging with the musical concepts. I also came away with a new skill having been tasked with writing out a piece of music for our final project. Now I'll be able to write out little compositions. I am very happy I took tis class!
It's a great class. Really relaxed and enjoyable and a great way to learn some music theory. It was fun nearly every time. The work doesn't take too long either.
Take it if you want an introduction to music/music theory; it's pretty straightforward.
A basic introduction to music theory. Would recommend it.

I would highly recommend this course for those wishing to receive a thorough introduction to music theory. There can be a lot of homework at times, which is very necessary to understand unfamiliar concepts, but it's not difficult. Musicians and non-musicians can appreciate this course.
